BROADCAST JOIN - A broadcast join is a join optimization where Spark sends (broadcasts) a small table to all worker nodes, so the join can happen locally without shuffling the big table.
Instead of moving large data across the network, Spark sends the small table everywhere.

🔹 When to use
✔ One table is small (few MBs)
✔ Other table is large
✔ Join key is common
