How to Detect Data Skew in Spark UI (Real Scenario)
Step 1: Open Spark UI
In Databricks:
👉 Go to:
Cluster → Spark UI → Stages

🔹 Step 2: Look at Stages
You’ll see multiple stages like:
Stage 1  → Completed
Stage 2  → Running
Stage 3  → Completed
👉 Click the stage related to:
join
groupBy
shuffle

🔹 Step 3: Check Tasks Tab
Inside the stage → go to Tasks
👉 This is where skew becomes visible 👇
🔥 What Skew Looks Like
❌ Normal (No Skew)
Task 1 → 5 sec
Task 2 → 6 sec
Task 3 → 5 sec
Task 4 → 6 sec

👉 All tasks take similar time ✅
🚨 Skewed Data
Task 1 → 5 sec
Task 2 → 6 sec
Task 3 → 5 sec
Task 4 → 120 sec ❌🔥
👉 One task is VERY slow

