DELETION VECTORS - Deletion Vectors (DV) are a feature in Delta Lake (used in Databricks) that allow Spark to logically delete rows without rewriting the data files.

how it works - 
        consider we have a file with 100 records now if we delete 20rows from it, then it will create new parquet file with 80records by keeping old parquet file with 100 records [because parquet files are immutable- can't change]
        in delection vectors, instead of creating new file again, it will create a delection vector log which will be in binary format, which store the information[index] about the deleted records. when we query it will go the logs and check the index and then remove the reocrds

        ❌ Without Deletion Vectors
        When you delete/update data:
        File A (100 rows)
        → delete 2 rows
        Spark must:
        rewrite entire file ❌
        create new file
        👉 Expensive + slow

        ✅ With Deletion Vectors
        File A (100 rows)
        → mark rows 5 and 20 as deleted
        → store this info separately
        👉 No file rewrite needed 🚀 

