PREDICTIVE I/O -  Predictive I/O (in Databricks / Lakehouse context) is a performance optimization feature that helps the system intelligently predict which data files are needed and reduces unnecessary data scanning and I/O operations.
- it perdicts whar data files will be needed next, based on query plans and part patterns
- it start reading those file into memory before spark actually needs them

result - fast query, especially for large data scans

in databricks, while creating a cluster we have a option to enable the PHOTON -- by enabling this predictive I/O will work automatically..

